The '''British Society for the History of Pharmacy''' is the organisation in the United Kingdom devoted to the [[history of pharmacy]].<ref>[http://www.bshp.org/bshpwebsite/index.htm Home.] British Society for the History of Pharmacy. Retrieved 21 September 2015.</ref> It was established in 1967, although its roots date back to 1952, when the Council of the Pharmaceutical Society established a history of pharmacy committee. The society has published a journal, the ''Pharmaceutical Historian'', since 1967.<ref>[http://www.bshp.org/bshpwebsite/Newsletter.htm Pharmaceutical Historian.] British Society for the History of Pharmacy. Retrieved 21 September 2015.</ref> It is affiliated to the [[British Society for the History of Medicine]]. The President of the society is [[Peter Homan]].

