{{about-distinguish|Filipino historian Maria Serena Diokno|Maria Lourdes Sereno{{!}}Chief Justice Maria Lourdes Sereno}} '''Maria Serena I. Diokno''', sometimes known by her nickname as '''Maris Diokno''',<ref name="JuaniyoArcellana20110612">{{Cite magazine |last=Arcellana |first=Juaniyo |date=2011-06-12 |title=Mariz Diokno remembers two Joses |url=https://www.philstar.com/other-sections/starweek-magazine/2011/06/12/695148/mariz-diokno-remembers-two-joses |magazine=StarWeek Magazine |location=Port Area, Manila, Philippines |publisher=Philippine Star Printing Co., Inc. |access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref> is a [[Filipino people|Filipino]] historian, academic, and former government official best known<ref name="PattyPasion20161201">{{Cite news |url=https://www.rappler.com/nation/154139-diokno-history-education-anti-marcos |title=Diokno: Next anti-Marcos campaign is to educate the youth |last=Pasion |first=Patty |date=2016-12-01 |work=Rappler |access-date=2018-09-15 |language=en}}</ref> for having served as chair of the [[National Historical Commission of the Philippines]]<ref name="RegineCabato20161205">{{Cite news |url=http://cnnphilippines.com/news/2016/12/02/Historical-commission-chair-diokno-SC-Duterte-consider-history.html |title=Former Historical Commission Chair: Supreme Court, Duterte must revisit history |last=Cabato |first=Regine |date=2016-12-05 |work=CNN Philippines |access-date=2018-09-15 |language=en}}</ref> and as a high-ranking official of the [[University of the Philippines]] system.<ref name="UNTV20140623">{{Cite news |url=https://www.untvweb.com/news/ched-inirekomendang-magkaroon-ng-9-units-na-ituturo-sa-wikang-filipino-sa-kolehiyo/ |title=CHED, inirekomendang magkaroon ng 9 units na ituturo sa wikang Filipino sa kolehiyo |date=2014-06-23 |work=UNTV News |access-date=2018-09-15 |publisher=UNTV-Breakthrough and Milestones Productions International (BMPI) |location=[[Quezon City]] |language=Tagalog}}</ref>
She is the daughter of Filipino Nationalist figure and legislator [[Jose Diokno]], the sister of human rights advocate [[Chel Diokno]], and the aunt of [[Philippine new wave|Filipino independent film]] [[auteur]] [[Pepe Diokno (director)|Pepe Diokno]].<ref name=dalisaybio>{{cite web|last=Dalisay|first=Jose Jr.|authorlink=|title=Jose W. Diokno: The Scholar-Warrior|work=|publisher=|date=|url=http://diokno.org/about|format=|doi=|accessdate=2011-03-03}}</ref><ref name="SaturOcampo20120225">{{Cite news |url=https://www.philstar.com/opinion/2012/02/25/780584/jose-ka-pepe-diokno-quintessential-nationalist |title=Jose 'Ka Pepe' Diokno, quintessential nationalist |last=Ocampo |first=Satur |date=2012-02-25 |work=The Philippine Star |access-date=2018-09-15}}</ref>
