'''Robert Montgomerie''' is a novelist and teacher. He read [[Greats]] at [[Oxford University]] and taught at [[St Edward's School, Oxford]],<ref>[http://www.yarletschool.org/index.php/Governors-and-Staff.html Yarlet School Governors' Website]</ref> and, from 1969 until retirement in 1998,<ref>News from Rugby School (NFRS) [http://www.rugbyschool.net/events/nfrs/NFRS_summer_97.pdf "Team Work and Fun"] Summer 1997, no. 13, p. 3</ref><ref>News from Rugby School (NFRS) [http://www.rugbyschool.net/events/nfrs/NFRS_spring_97.pdf "Deputy Head To Be"] Spring 1997, no. 12, p. 4</ref> at [[Rugby School]].<ref>News from Rugby School (NFRS) [http://www.rugbyschool.net/events/nfrs/NFRS_autumn_95.pdf "Celebrity Cricket"] Autumn 1995, no. 11, p. 14</ref> He taught both [[Latin]] and [[Greek language|Greek]], but specialised in [[ancient history]] and [[classical civilisation]].
Robert is a member of the [[Classical Association]] and the [[Joint Association of Classical Teachers]]. He also is the Managing Editor for [[Sparta (magazine)|''Sparta'' - Journal of Ancient Spartan and Greek History]].<ref>[http://www.sparta.markoulakispublications.org.uk/?s=about Sparta Journal Editorial Online]</ref>
In 2008, he released his first history novel, with title, ''Helot: A Story of Ancient Sparta'' ({{ISBN|978-0955747410}}).
